37575>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37575>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37575>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37578>>>
37578>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37578>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37578>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37578>>>        Case Begin
37578>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37580>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37580>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37580>>>                Case Break
37581>>>                
37581>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37584>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37584>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37584>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37584>>>                Case Break
37585>>>                
37585>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37588>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37588>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37588>>>                Case Break
37589>>>                
37589>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37589>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37589>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37589>>>                  
37589>>>        Case End
37589>>>
37589>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37589>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37589>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37590>>>
37590>>>    End_Procedure
37591>>>
37591>>>End_Object
