38200>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38200>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38200>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38203>>>
38203>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38203>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38203>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38203>>>        Case Begin
38203>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38205>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38205>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38205>>>                Case Break
38206>>>                
38206>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38209>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38209>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38209>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38209>>>                Case Break
38210>>>                
38210>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38213>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38213>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38213>>>                Case Break
38214>>>                
38214>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38214>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38214>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38214>>>                  
38214>>>        Case End
38214>>>
38214>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38214>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38214>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38215>>>
38215>>>    End_Procedure
38216>>>
38216>>>End_Object
